summary: so last night I was hanging with my mom and I asked if I could record Running Wild with Bear Grylls and she of course asked why...
body:
so last night I was hanging with my mom and I asked if I could record Running Wild with Bear Grylls and she of course asked why cause that’s not typically the kinda show I watch it’s way more my dad’s thing. so I said it was cause the next episode is gonna have Brie Larson on it and I wanted to see it. she starts laughing and she says “dang you got it bad for her huh?” and the fear in me of being closeted most of my life was like whaaaat and she says “she’s your big crush right now” but the way she said it was so…normal? it was just something to tease me over and fun to talk about. so I did. I gushed a little and we both laughed about it and she said she did look pretty cute with the haircut they gave her in Endgame. and then we went back to watching Good Girls.

idk man I just…if you had told me a decade ago when I was 16 that this conversation would happen with no disgust or malice or lack of love I would have laughed in your face. I guess what I’m trying to say is that sometimes it does get better. sometimes you get to sit with your mom who has learned that not everything is how she saw it years ago and that her prejudices were holding her back from loving me fully. and you’ll get to joke and talk openly because it will be your normal and her normal too.

don’t give up.
